nload PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531808\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531808\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 24, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rvk1665702925977.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rvk1665702925977.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rvk1665702925977.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rvk1665702925977\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Overflow Tables\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__overflow_tables_141845\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">DBMSs may impose upper limits to the number of fields in a table, the length of a field, and the length of a record. Some DBMSs do not support variable-length fields with a high maximum length. To overcome these limitations, Uniface provides an overflow mechanism, in which data that is represented as a single modeled entity is automatically split into two tables—the base table and an overflow table.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__p_d47024e1_d47025e1_d47026e1\">The base table contains all the fixed-length fields plus the first part of the variable data in the occurrence. The overflow table contains the rest of the variable-length data. An overflow table contains the primary key from the base table and the overflow information from the field that causes the overflow table. The name of an overflow table consists of the same name as the lowercase entity name with the prefix <code class=\"ph codeph\">o</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__note_w2630ab1b5b5_w2631ab1b5_w2632ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The overflow mechanism is a\n      technical encoding for larger amounts of data and is not transparent for other applications.\n      When transparency is required, use segmented fields that result in Text and Image data types.\n      For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dpo1665702777219.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dpo1665702777219.html\" title=\"Segmented fields provide an alternative storage method for large amounts of data that would be impractical to store in a normal database column. Large data objects can include audio- and video clips, or objects that functionally belong to other applications but are under the control of Uniface. Such objects are referred to as Binary Large Objects (BLOBs).\">Segmented Fields: String Packing Codes (SC and SU)</a>. </div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__p_d47027e1_d47028e1_d47029e1\">The amount of variable-length data that is maintained in the base table depends on the DBMS.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__p_d47030e1_d47031e1_d47032e1\">Uniface automatically creates overflow tables in the following circumstances:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23420e1_d23421e1_d23422e1\">When the entity contains one or more fields defined using variable-length packing codes:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23423e1_d23424e1_d23425e1\">C*\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23426e1_d23427e1_d23428e1\">R*\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23429e1_d23430e1_d23431e1\">U*\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23432e1_d23433e1_d23434e1\">W*\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23435e1_d23436e1_d23437e1\">VC*\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23438e1_d23439e1_d23440e1\">VR*\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23441e1_d23442e1_d23443e1\">VU*\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23444e1_d23445e1_d23446e1\">VW*\n </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23447e1_d23448e1_d23449e1\">When the entity contains one or more fields defined\n                                using segmented string fields (packing codes ‘SC*’ and so on), and\n                                the DBMS for that entity does not support this feature. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__li_d23450e1_d23451e1_d23452e1\">When the data size of the occurrence being written\n                                is larger than the maximum size supported by the DBMS in use. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__p_d47033e1_d47034e1_d47035e1\">The Uniface connector interface automatically performs all the I/O needed to create and maintain overflow tables and to store and retrieve occurrences from it.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"rvk1665702925977__note_w2633ab1b5c15_w2634ab1b5_w2635ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> If overflow tables are created, remember to back them up with the rest of your data.</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531808\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531808\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Overflow Tables Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 24, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Overflow Tables DBMSs may impose upper limits to the number of fields in a table, the length of a field, and the length of a record. Some DBMSs do not support variable-length fields with a high maximum length. To overcome these limitations, Uniface provides an overflow mechanism, in which data that is represented as a single modeled entity is automatically split into two tables—the base table and an overflow table. The base table contains all the fixed-length fields plus the first part of the variable data in the occurrence. The overflow table contains the rest of the variable-length data. An overflow table contains the primary key from the base table and the overflow information from the field that causes the overflow table. The name of an overflow table consists of the same name as the lowercase entity name with the prefix o . Note: The overflow mechanism is a technical encoding for larger amounts of data and is not transparent for other applications. When transparency is required, use segmented fields that result in Text and Image data types. For more information, see Segmented Fields: String Packing Codes (SC and SU) . The amount of variable-length data that is maintained in the base table depends on the DBMS. Uniface automatically creates overflow tables in the following circumstances: When the entity contains one or more fields defined using variable-length packing codes: C* R* U* W* VC* VR* VU* VW* When the entity contains one or more fields defined using segmented string fields (packing codes ‘SC*’ and so on), and the DBMS for that entity does not support this feature. When the data size of the occurrence being written is larger than the maximum size supported by the DBMS in use. The Uniface connector interface automatically performs all the I/O needed to create and maintain overflow tables and to store and retrieve occurrences from it. CAUTION: If overflow tables are created, remember to back them up with the rest of your data. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}